  "prompt": "What is a recipe like Whole Foods mock chicken salad?",
  "response": "Here's a simple recipe inspired by Whole Foods' mock chicken salad that you can make at home. This vegan version typically uses chickpeas or tofu as the base, along with a blend of spices and other ingredients to achieve a delicious flavor. \n\n### Vegan Chickpea Salad\n\n**Ingredients:**\n\n- 1 can (15 oz) chickpeas, drained and rinsed\n- 1/4 cup vegan mayonnaise (adjust for creaminess to your liking)\n- 1 tablespoon Dijon mustard\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon onion powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1-2 stalks celery, diced\n- 1/4 red onion, diced\n- 1/2 cup grapes, halved (optional)\n- 1/4 cup chopped walnuts or pecans (optional)\n- Fresh herbs like parsley or dill, chopped (optional)\n\n**Instructions:**\n\n1. **Prepare the Chickpeas:** In a large mixing bowl, use a fork or potato masher to slightly mash the chickpeas. You want them to be broken down but still have some texture.\n\n2. **Mix the Dressing:** In a separate bowl, mix together the vegan mayonnaise, Dijon mustard, lemon juice, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and pepper. Taste and adjust seasoning as necessary.\n\n3. **Combine Ingredients:** Add the diced celery, red onion, grapes, walnuts, and any herbs to the mashed chickpeas. Pour the dressing over the chickpea mixture and stir until everything is well combined.\n\n4. **Chill:** Refrigerate the salad for at least 30 minutes to allow the flavors to meld.\n\n5. **Serve:** Enjoy your chickpea salad on a bed of greens, in a sandwich, or with crackers.\n\n### Tips:\n- You can customize the salad by adding ingredients like diced bell peppers, avocado, or chopped pickles.\n- For a smoky flavor, consider adding a little smoked paprika.\n- If you prefer a different base, you can substitute chickpeas with crumbled tofu or seitan.\n\nEnjoy your homemade mock chicken salad!",
